cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a new networking architecture for the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions security concerns in information-centric networking and proposes an alternative architecture, which may be of interest to the cryptography and security community. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the complexities of forwarding data by name and proposes an alternative architecture that reduces the storage and processing requirements in relaying nodes, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the limitations of the algorithms used in Named Data Networking (NDN) and Content-Centric Networking (CCNx) and proposes an alternative architecture, which may be of interest to the data structures and algorithms community. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new networking architecture that aims to improve the efficiency of content access, dissemination, and storage, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
